		<div id="comment_body_64526787">It is actually an excuse for the management to not <em>commit</em> to what they specify and to instead change their mind twice a week. And to make this seem more legit and obfuscate the lack of a solid plan, you add meetings to waste half of your working time. Scrum especially is like communism, the proponents says "it's good, you're just doing it wrong", but I have not seen any evidence of it working well for anyone. I've also done Kanban, which does work much better basically by removing most of the useless meetin</div>
